reviews.text: Wonderful food and service! Try their very best to serve customers. My husband and I ordered different soups, they divided each bowl of soup into two smaller portions so my husband and I could try both! Very considerate! Cook and serve with heart! The best restaurant I’ve ever been to in Hong Kong!
Not bad
今天和家人慶祝大兒子17歲生日。他選擇了吃法國菜。於是我們來了離家不遠又遠離繁囂的Chez Les Copians 。主廚Bonnie 為我們設計菜式，不用我們費心，讓我們吃了一頓海陸空齊備又稱心滿意的晚餐。

result.name: Chez Les Copains

reviews.text: Super impressive dinner with my best friends.  Highly recommended this restaurant because the chef is so passionate, but you must make reservations, otherwise, you might be hitting the locked door.
Cozy environment and great food. Highly recommend making reservations in advance.

Environment scored the most. The restaurant is small. Can only house 10 people max. So the chef herself served us. It is romantic to have dinner with French music playing. 

We order escargot, andoulliete, 15 days aged tenderloin, skate wing. I like the tenderloin. Taste is good after aged. Andoulliete is pig intestine. It has a bit ammonia taste. So we don't quite like it. Surprisingly, skate wing also taste a bit ammonia.Escargot is above average standard.Desert is meringue. Very good I like it

A French restaurant on a small outlying Hong Kong island, amazing! What a gem.  Good wine, cheeses and assortment of meats. With outdoor seating. we like the relaxed laid back feel. Service can be somewhat spotty, but hey, I did say 'relaxed and laid back'. There's a bonus .. customers may play petanque on the small clearing by the  sidewall of the shop
Show less
Guess the name says it all
